# Obsidian chat context memory (Wist)
#
# Goal: keep long-running app context across separate chats by writing concise
# session notes into the repo-backed Obsidian vault.
#
# Scope: This rule applies to this repository only.
#
# When to write
# - After any non-trivial change set (features, architecture, build scripts, diagnostics, tests).
# - After receiving important runtime evidence from the user (logs, screenshots, reproduction steps).
# - Prefer writing once per “milestone” / problem solved, not after every trivial message.
#
# Where to write
# - Always update (at least) the current session note under:
#   `ObsidianVault/10-Project-Wist/Sessions/YYYY-MM-DD — <short-title>.md`
# - If the work changes user-visible behavior or introduces a new subsystem, also update:
#   `ObsidianVault/10-Project-Wist/Architecture.md` and/or `Roadmap.md` and/or `Backlog.md`.
#
# What to write (keep it short)
# - 5–15 bullets max:
#   - what changed (file/module names)
#   - why (root cause / user story)
#   - how to verify (commands / UI path)
#   - any known follow-ups / risks
#
# Constraints
# - Do NOT paste large logs verbatim; summarize and link to where they were obtained.
# - Do NOT store secrets (passwords, tokens, API keys) in Obsidian or code.
# - Do NOT duplicate full code; keep high-level notes + file paths.

